    <nav>
      <ul class="menu">
        <li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="modern.html">Modern Web Servers</a></li>
        <li><a href="history.html">History</a></li>
        <li><a href="references.html">References</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>
  <main>
    <h2>Current Technologies</h2>
    <p>Popular modern web servers include Apache, Nginx, and IIS. Apache is highly configurable and open-source, Nginx excels in high-concurrency environments, and IIS integrates with Microsoft ecosystems.</p>
    <h3>Comparison Table</h3>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Server</th><th>Strengths</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Apache</td><td>Flexible, Open-source, Modular</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Nginx</td><td>Performance, Scalability, Lightweight</td></tr>
      <tr><td>IIS</td><td>Windows Integration, Security, GUI-based</td></tr>
    </table>
    <h3>Deployment Trends</h3>
    <p>Cloud platforms and containerized environments are increasingly popular. Servers are now deployed using Docker and Kubernetes, often as part of CI/CD pipelines.</p>
  </main>
