  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>History of Web Servers</h1>
    <nav>
      <ul class="menu">
        <li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="modern.html">Modern Web Servers</a></li>
        <li><a href="history.html">History</a></li>
        <li><a href="references.html">References</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>
  <main>
    <h2>Early Development</h2>
    <p>The first web server was developed by Tim Berners-Lee at CERN in 1989. It ran on a NeXT computer and hosted the first website at http://info.cern.ch.</p>
    <h2>Evolution</h2>
    <p>Apache HTTP Server launched in 1995 and became dominant due to its open-source nature and extensibility. Nginx followed in 2004, focusing on high performance and low memory usage.</p>
  </main>
